   <concept id="FAR_46_705" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">46.705</ph> Limitations.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2697e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2724e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            Except for the warranties in the clauses at <xref href="52.246-3.dita#FAR_52_246_3"
                        base="i1046895"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.246-3</xref>, Inspection of Supplies-Cost-Reimbursement, and <xref href="52.246-8.dita#FAR_52_246_8"
                        base="i1047007"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.246-8</xref>, Inspection of Research and Development-Cost-Reimbursement, the contracting officer shall not include warranties in cost-reimbursement contracts, unless authorized in accordance with agency regulations (see <xref href="46.708.dita#FAR_46_708"
                        base="i1071923"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">46.708</xref>).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2724e24">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            Warranty clauses shall not limit the Government’s rights under an inspection clause (see <xref href="Subpart_46.3.dita#FAR_Subpart_46_3"
                        base="i1072238"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  46.3</xref>) in relation to latent defects, fraud, or gross mistakes that amount to fraud.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2724e32">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
						            Except for warranty clauses in construction contracts, warranty clauses shall provide that the warranty applies notwithstanding inspection and acceptance or other clauses or terms of the contract.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
